WEBVTT

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:02.830 align:middle line:90%


00:00:02.830 --> 00:00:05.260 align:middle line:84%
>> Hi, I'm Georgia Shakti-Hill,
and I want to invite you

00:00:05.260 --> 00:00:07.340 align:middle line:90%
to join us today on a journey.

00:00:07.340 --> 00:00:11.050 align:middle line:84%
We're going to be going on
an invisible path to success.

00:00:11.050 --> 00:00:14.530 align:middle line:84%
Our guide will be the author
of the book Robert Scheinfeld.

00:00:14.530 --> 00:00:16.239 align:middle line:84%
So come join us,
"Living in Balance."

00:00:16.239 --> 00:00:17.710 align:middle line:84%
I'm Shakti-Hill,
and we will take

00:00:17.710 --> 00:00:21.348 align:middle line:84%
a journey on the
invisible path to success.

00:00:21.348 --> 00:00:24.834 align:middle line:90%
[MUSIC PLAYING]

00:00:24.834 --> 00:00:37.790 align:middle line:90%


00:00:37.790 --> 00:00:42.170 align:middle line:10%
Just the word success might
enthrall us and invite us.

00:00:42.170 --> 00:00:45.530 align:middle line:10%
I was reading the introduction
to the book by Bob Scheinfeld,

00:00:45.530 --> 00:00:46.710 align:middle line:10%
and I really liked it.

00:00:46.710 --> 00:00:48.410 align:middle line:10%
It just sounded so intriguing.

00:00:48.410 --> 00:00:50.940 align:middle line:10%
And the invisible path,
that's the exciting part,

00:00:50.940 --> 00:00:53.670 align:middle line:10%
to find out why is it invisible
and what does that mean?

00:00:53.670 --> 00:00:55.400 align:middle line:10%
He said the definitions
are new, so we

00:00:55.400 --> 00:00:57.080 align:middle line:10%
have Bob to explain this to us.

00:00:57.080 --> 00:00:58.090 align:middle line:90%
Welcome.

00:00:58.090 --> 00:00:59.360 align:middle line:90%
>> Glad to be here.

00:00:59.360 --> 00:01:00.880 align:middle line:84%
>> The invisible
path to success.

00:01:00.880 --> 00:01:01.680 align:middle line:90%
I love it.

00:01:01.680 --> 00:01:02.555 align:middle line:90%
That's a great title.

00:01:02.555 --> 00:01:04.892 align:middle line:84%
But tell me, I don't
know what that means.

00:01:04.892 --> 00:01:06.350 align:middle line:84%
>> Well, people
are always saying--

00:01:06.350 --> 00:01:07.770 align:middle line:84%
and it's a big
term in computers--

00:01:07.770 --> 00:01:09.150 align:middle line:90%
what you see is what you get.

00:01:09.150 --> 00:01:09.950 align:middle line:90%
>> OK.

00:01:09.950 --> 00:01:13.045 align:middle line:84%
>> It's actually what you don't
see is what you get in life.

00:01:13.045 --> 00:01:14.420 align:middle line:84%
I'm a big believer
that there are

00:01:14.420 --> 00:01:17.900 align:middle line:84%
what I call unseen forces
that shape our lives.

00:01:17.900 --> 00:01:19.880 align:middle line:84%
And my book shows
people how to understand

00:01:19.880 --> 00:01:22.250 align:middle line:84%
what those forces are
and how to better manage

00:01:22.250 --> 00:01:24.980 align:middle line:84%
them to go about getting
what you really want in life.

00:01:24.980 --> 00:01:27.770 align:middle line:84%
>> And there are seven steps
that you take people through

00:01:27.770 --> 00:01:30.560 align:middle line:90%
to manage those unseen--

00:01:30.560 --> 00:01:32.260 align:middle line:90%
>> Those unseen forces, yeah.

00:01:32.260 --> 00:01:35.510 align:middle line:84%
>> OK, well, also you said you
had an audience that you kind

00:01:35.510 --> 00:01:37.010 align:middle line:90%
of targeted with this book.

00:01:37.010 --> 00:01:41.240 align:middle line:84%
Who do you think is going to
be choosing this book to read,

00:01:41.240 --> 00:01:44.007 align:middle line:84%
and why did you want to target
this particular audience?

00:01:44.007 --> 00:01:46.340 align:middle line:84%
>> Well, I think there are
more and more people that are

00:01:46.340 --> 00:01:49.200 align:middle line:84%
starting to ask what I call
the most important questions

00:01:49.200 --> 00:01:50.000 align:middle line:90%
in life.

00:01:50.000 --> 00:01:51.230 align:middle line:10%
Who am I?

00:01:51.230 --> 00:01:52.400 align:middle line:10%
Why am I here?

00:01:52.400 --> 00:01:54.260 align:middle line:10%
What is my life purpose?

00:01:54.260 --> 00:01:56.875 align:middle line:84%
What really causes what
happens to me every day?

00:01:56.875 --> 00:01:58.250 align:middle line:84%
And if there's
something I really

00:01:58.250 --> 00:02:00.223 align:middle line:84%
want, how do I really
go about getting it?

00:02:00.223 --> 00:02:02.390 align:middle line:84%
How do I get from here to
where I really want to be?

00:02:02.390 --> 00:02:05.150 align:middle line:84%
And they're frustrated by
the traditional answers,

00:02:05.150 --> 00:02:06.650 align:middle line:84%
and they're looking
for new answers.

00:02:06.650 --> 00:02:09.680 align:middle line:84%
And I wanted to offer
some different answers

00:02:09.680 --> 00:02:12.140 align:middle line:84%
based on some experiences
I had with my life

00:02:12.140 --> 00:02:14.720 align:middle line:84%
falling apart using the
traditional self-help

00:02:14.720 --> 00:02:16.310 align:middle line:84%
techniques to try
and change things,

00:02:16.310 --> 00:02:19.250 align:middle line:84%
finding they didn't work,
needing to find something

00:02:19.250 --> 00:02:21.190 align:middle line:84%
that worked because my
life was a real mess.

00:02:21.190 --> 00:02:22.160 align:middle line:90%
It was falling apart.

00:02:22.160 --> 00:02:24.830 align:middle line:84%
And coming up with some
answers that worked for me,

00:02:24.830 --> 00:02:27.440 align:middle line:84%
and I found it worked
for other people as well.

00:02:27.440 --> 00:02:30.110 align:middle line:84%
>> And what I like about
that is that it's always--

00:02:30.110 --> 00:02:33.590 align:middle line:84%
it seems as if it's out
of the need that we come

00:02:33.590 --> 00:02:35.000 align:middle line:90%
to the answers.

00:02:35.000 --> 00:02:38.060 align:middle line:84%
Because there was a need in
your life to figure out what

00:02:38.060 --> 00:02:39.560 align:middle line:90%
you had to do next.

00:02:39.560 --> 00:02:41.480 align:middle line:84%
We have a few
graphics that we're

00:02:41.480 --> 00:02:43.438 align:middle line:84%
going to bring up that
come from your book.

00:02:43.438 --> 00:02:45.230 align:middle line:10%
The first one that I
wanted you to explain,

00:02:45.230 --> 00:02:46.250 align:middle line:10%
and you said that
you're going to be

00:02:46.250 --> 00:02:47.820 align:middle line:10%
looking at this differently.

00:02:47.820 --> 00:02:53.270 align:middle line:10%
And these are the seven steps
to understanding and managing

00:02:53.270 --> 00:02:55.670 align:middle line:10%
the unseen forces
shaping your life.

00:02:55.670 --> 00:02:56.640 align:middle line:10%
Wow.

00:02:56.640 --> 00:02:59.810 align:middle line:10%
[LAUGH] That's what
we're learning here.

00:02:59.810 --> 00:03:02.205 align:middle line:10%
And the first one is
about the director.

00:03:02.205 --> 00:03:03.830 align:middle line:84%
And you said you're
going to be looking

00:03:03.830 --> 00:03:07.040 align:middle line:84%
at the director of your life
maybe differently than most

00:03:07.040 --> 00:03:08.585 align:middle line:90%
people would define that.

00:03:08.585 --> 00:03:11.880 align:middle line:84%
>> Well, when you go to a movie,
you see a lot of action up

00:03:11.880 --> 00:03:12.680 align:middle line:90%
on the screen.

00:03:12.680 --> 00:03:14.300 align:middle line:84%
You see actors, and
you see actresses,

00:03:14.300 --> 00:03:16.160 align:middle line:90%
and you see special effects.

00:03:16.160 --> 00:03:19.910 align:middle line:84%
What you're not aware of is
the director of the movie, who

00:03:19.910 --> 00:03:23.090 align:middle line:84%
coached those actors and
actresses, paced the movie,

00:03:23.090 --> 00:03:25.160 align:middle line:84%
made decisions about what's
going to happen where

00:03:25.160 --> 00:03:27.618 align:middle line:84%
and what order, how are we
going to communicate and explore

00:03:27.618 --> 00:03:30.170 align:middle line:84%
this whole idea that
the movie is about.

00:03:30.170 --> 00:03:32.370 align:middle line:84%
And the same thing
is true in our lives.

00:03:32.370 --> 00:03:36.050 align:middle line:84%
We all come into life wanting
to explore or experience or do

00:03:36.050 --> 00:03:37.768 align:middle line:84%
something, just
like somebody who

00:03:37.768 --> 00:03:40.310 align:middle line:84%
makes a movie because there's
an idea or a theme or something

00:03:40.310 --> 00:03:41.968 align:middle line:90%
they want to explore.

00:03:41.968 --> 00:03:43.760 align:middle line:84%
And in the movie, the
director of the movie

00:03:43.760 --> 00:03:46.190 align:middle line:84%
manages all the details
from behind the scenes

00:03:46.190 --> 00:03:49.350 align:middle line:84%
with a crew to make sure
that that movie gets made.

00:03:49.350 --> 00:03:50.150 align:middle line:90%
Same thing.

00:03:50.150 --> 00:03:51.950 align:middle line:84%
There is another part
of our consciousness

00:03:51.950 --> 00:03:54.530 align:middle line:84%
that I compare to the director
of the movie, who we're here

00:03:54.530 --> 00:03:56.900 align:middle line:84%
playing and having the
experience, and this part of us

00:03:56.900 --> 00:03:59.930 align:middle line:84%
is behind us managing
all the details for us

00:03:59.930 --> 00:04:02.390 align:middle line:84%
to make sure that we get what
I call the total immersion

00:04:02.390 --> 00:04:04.430 align:middle line:84%
movie experience
we came here for.

00:04:04.430 --> 00:04:06.380 align:middle line:84%
>> OK, so it isn't
separate from us.

00:04:06.380 --> 00:04:08.600 align:middle line:84%
It's a part of us,
and it's the director

00:04:08.600 --> 00:04:10.750 align:middle line:84%
who is a part of us who
is directing our life.

00:04:10.750 --> 00:04:11.905 align:middle line:84%
Is that how you're
explaining this?

00:04:11.905 --> 00:04:12.360 align:middle line:90%
>> Yes.

00:04:12.360 --> 00:04:13.160 align:middle line:90%
>> OK.

00:04:13.160 --> 00:04:16.700 align:middle line:84%
>> It's another part of us that
takes over the responsibility

00:04:16.700 --> 00:04:17.737 align:middle line:90%
for managing.

00:04:17.737 --> 00:04:20.029 align:middle line:84%
The way I explain it is you
look at a very famous actor

00:04:20.029 --> 00:04:21.440 align:middle line:90%
like Tom Hanks.

00:04:21.440 --> 00:04:22.780 align:middle line:90%
Tom Hanks is a real person.

00:04:22.780 --> 00:04:23.660 align:middle line:90%
He's got a real life.

00:04:23.660 --> 00:04:24.460 align:middle line:90%
He does things.

00:04:24.460 --> 00:04:26.780 align:middle line:84%
But when he's onstage,
he temporarily

00:04:26.780 --> 00:04:28.640 align:middle line:90%
leaves who he really is behind.

00:04:28.640 --> 00:04:30.080 align:middle line:90%
He takes on another persona.

00:04:30.080 --> 00:04:31.350 align:middle line:90%
He has this experience.

00:04:31.350 --> 00:04:33.780 align:middle line:84%
And when it's over, he goes
back to his regular life.

00:04:33.780 --> 00:04:34.580 align:middle line:90%
>> Yes.

00:04:34.580 --> 00:04:37.010 align:middle line:84%
>> So there's a part of
us that comes down here,

00:04:37.010 --> 00:04:39.060 align:middle line:84%
has this total immersion
movie experience.

00:04:39.060 --> 00:04:42.380 align:middle line:84%
And the real us, if you
will, stays behind the scenes

00:04:42.380 --> 00:04:44.090 align:middle line:84%
and manages all the
details to make sure

00:04:44.090 --> 00:04:45.580 align:middle line:90%
we get the experience we want.

00:04:45.580 --> 00:04:47.570 align:middle line:84%
>> OK, so we are the
director of our movie.

00:04:47.570 --> 00:04:48.370 align:middle line:90%
>> Yes.

00:04:48.370 --> 00:04:49.420 align:middle line:90%
>> OK, I like that.

00:04:49.420 --> 00:04:50.220 align:middle line:90%
Now you said--

00:04:50.220 --> 00:04:52.622 align:middle line:84%
>> But the conscious
part of us isn't.

00:04:52.622 --> 00:04:53.830 align:middle line:90%
>> The conscious part is not.

00:04:53.830 --> 00:04:55.640 align:middle line:84%
>> The conscious part
is not running the show.

00:04:55.640 --> 00:04:58.140 align:middle line:84%
That's one of the big messages
in the book that's different.

00:04:58.140 --> 00:04:59.427 align:middle line:90%
This director part of us is.

00:04:59.427 --> 00:05:01.760 align:middle line:84%
>> One of the things that I
have found of people who are

00:05:01.760 --> 00:05:03.830 align:middle line:84%
on the spiritual path
and they are aware of it,

00:05:03.830 --> 00:05:07.100 align:middle line:84%
they are in search of
that purpose in life.

00:05:07.100 --> 00:05:10.910 align:middle line:84%
And as you put it, it's
discovering your true self

00:05:10.910 --> 00:05:13.100 align:middle line:90%
and your true life's purpose.

00:05:13.100 --> 00:05:16.310 align:middle line:84%
And that is really why
we're here, is it not?

00:05:16.310 --> 00:05:19.490 align:middle line:84%
That's a big deal for you
to explain to your reader.

00:05:19.490 --> 00:05:21.530 align:middle line:90%
How would you explain this?

00:05:21.530 --> 00:05:24.950 align:middle line:84%
How does someone find their
true self and their true life's

00:05:24.950 --> 00:05:25.910 align:middle line:90%
purpose?

00:05:25.910 --> 00:05:27.840 align:middle line:84%
>> Well, let me
ask you a question.

00:05:27.840 --> 00:05:31.135 align:middle line:84%
What is something in life that
you just absolutely love to do?

00:05:31.135 --> 00:05:33.110 align:middle line:84%
>> Well, it's what
I'm doing right now.

00:05:33.110 --> 00:05:34.235 align:middle line:90%
>> OK, so doing interviews?

00:05:34.235 --> 00:05:34.490 align:middle line:90%
>> It is.

00:05:34.490 --> 00:05:35.290 align:middle line:90%
Absolutely.

00:05:35.290 --> 00:05:36.100 align:middle line:90%
I love it, yes.

00:05:36.100 --> 00:05:36.180 align:middle line:90%
>> OK.

00:05:36.180 --> 00:05:38.230 align:middle line:10%
What about it is
it that you love?

00:05:38.230 --> 00:05:41.210 align:middle line:10%
>> Well, I love to get that
information, and it's exciting,

00:05:41.210 --> 00:05:45.010 align:middle line:10%
especially when I'm interviewing
somebody who's sharing

00:05:45.010 --> 00:05:47.410 align:middle line:10%
something that they've
found to be profound,

00:05:47.410 --> 00:05:50.540 align:middle line:10%
and they can't wait to
share it with other people.

00:05:50.540 --> 00:05:51.790 align:middle line:90%
>> And that's exciting to you?

00:05:51.790 --> 00:05:52.748 align:middle line:90%
>> Oh, I love it, yeah.

00:05:52.748 --> 00:05:55.206 align:middle line:84%
>> OK, excitement to me is what
I call an inner experience.

00:05:55.206 --> 00:05:56.006 align:middle line:90%
>> OK.

00:05:56.006 --> 00:05:57.760 align:middle line:84%
>> To me, everything
that we do in life,

00:05:57.760 --> 00:06:00.160 align:middle line:84%
everything that we love to do,
whether it's horseback riding,

00:06:00.160 --> 00:06:02.140 align:middle line:84%
or it's interviewing, or
it's going to a movie,

00:06:02.140 --> 00:06:04.540 align:middle line:84%
or it's skating, or it's
singing, or listening to music,

00:06:04.540 --> 00:06:07.150 align:middle line:84%
anything you could ask
somebody that they love to do,

00:06:07.150 --> 00:06:10.520 align:middle line:84%
what it's really about is
what's going on inside of us.

00:06:10.520 --> 00:06:12.820 align:middle line:84%
It's what we're thinking,
it's what we're feeling,

00:06:12.820 --> 00:06:13.990 align:middle line:90%
and it's how we're growing.

00:06:13.990 --> 00:06:15.940 align:middle line:90%
It's the internal experience.

00:06:15.940 --> 00:06:17.110 align:middle line:90%
That's all that matters.

00:06:17.110 --> 00:06:19.060 align:middle line:84%
Everything that's out
on the screen of a movie

00:06:19.060 --> 00:06:22.270 align:middle line:84%
is all designed to impact
your internal experiences.

00:06:22.270 --> 00:06:24.100 align:middle line:84%
Everything you do
in life is designed

00:06:24.100 --> 00:06:26.410 align:middle line:84%
to impact your
internal experiences.

00:06:26.410 --> 00:06:30.040 align:middle line:84%
So to me, we all come into
life interested in exploring

00:06:30.040 --> 00:06:32.920 align:middle line:84%
a particular group
of inner experiences.

00:06:32.920 --> 00:06:34.978 align:middle line:84%
And we create this
whole movie script

00:06:34.978 --> 00:06:36.520 align:middle line:84%
and have the actors
and the actresses

00:06:36.520 --> 00:06:38.620 align:middle line:84%
and have all these things
that happen in our lives

00:06:38.620 --> 00:06:40.840 align:middle line:84%
to stimulate those inner
experiences that we're

00:06:40.840 --> 00:06:42.350 align:middle line:90%
really interested in.

00:06:42.350 --> 00:06:44.260 align:middle line:84%
So there's no
single life purpose.

00:06:44.260 --> 00:06:46.477 align:middle line:84%
We all come in here to
explore these different inner

00:06:46.477 --> 00:06:47.560 align:middle line:90%
experiences and interests.

00:06:47.560 --> 00:06:48.518 align:middle line:90%
And it can be anything.

00:06:48.518 --> 00:06:51.820 align:middle line:84%
I mean, it could be something
from being a mother of twins,

00:06:51.820 --> 00:06:55.390 align:middle line:84%
to being a doctor, to
being a spy behind enemy

00:06:55.390 --> 00:06:58.100 align:middle line:84%
lines in a war, to helping
to share personal growth

00:06:58.100 --> 00:06:58.900 align:middle line:90%
information.

00:06:58.900 --> 00:07:00.817 align:middle line:84%
Everyone is interested
in something different.

00:07:00.817 --> 00:07:04.060 align:middle line:84%
>> OK, but how we find that--
how we know we're in it is when

00:07:04.060 --> 00:07:06.850 align:middle line:84%
it's so exciting, it's the
excitement that we feel,

00:07:06.850 --> 00:07:10.120 align:middle line:84%
that inner excitement, then
we are kind of in that groove.

00:07:10.120 --> 00:07:11.660 align:middle line:90%
Is that what you're saying?

00:07:11.660 --> 00:07:14.082 align:middle line:84%
How do we know if
we are doing it?

00:07:14.082 --> 00:07:16.290 align:middle line:84%
>> Well, first of all, to
me, you're always doing it.

00:07:16.290 --> 00:07:16.660 align:middle line:90%
>> OK.

00:07:16.660 --> 00:07:18.190 align:middle line:84%
>> Whether you know of
it consciously or not,

00:07:18.190 --> 00:07:20.735 align:middle line:84%
this director part of you is
making sure that you're staying

00:07:20.735 --> 00:07:23.110 align:middle line:84%
on track and that everything
is moving the way it's meant

00:07:23.110 --> 00:07:25.402 align:middle line:84%
to move, and you're going to
have the movie experience,

00:07:25.402 --> 00:07:26.950 align:middle line:90%
the lifetime you came here for.

00:07:26.950 --> 00:07:29.200 align:middle line:84%
So you're always on track,
whether you feel it or not.

00:07:29.200 --> 00:07:33.010 align:middle line:84%
I know lots of times we don't,
but to me the truth is you are.

00:07:33.010 --> 00:07:35.440 align:middle line:84%
But it's all about what's
going on inside of you,

00:07:35.440 --> 00:07:37.960 align:middle line:84%
not what's going
on outside of you.

00:07:37.960 --> 00:07:41.770 align:middle line:84%
>> So that exhilaration that
we feel standing on the edge

00:07:41.770 --> 00:07:44.470 align:middle line:84%
of the Gulf of Mexico and
looking out at the sunset,

00:07:44.470 --> 00:07:48.070 align:middle line:84%
then that's just one of those
moments that we have that's one

00:07:48.070 --> 00:07:51.340 align:middle line:84%
of the reasons why we're here is
to experience this world, too?

00:07:51.340 --> 00:07:53.330 align:middle line:84%
Can it be just that
simple of experience?

00:07:53.330 --> 00:07:54.700 align:middle line:90%
>> To me it's just that simple.

00:07:54.700 --> 00:07:56.360 align:middle line:84%
Did you see the movie
"City of Angels"?

00:07:56.360 --> 00:07:57.160 align:middle line:90%
>> Yes.

00:07:57.160 --> 00:07:57.960 align:middle line:90%
Yes.

00:07:57.960 --> 00:08:00.910 align:middle line:84%
>> You have this angel who,
at least the way the movie was

00:08:00.910 --> 00:08:03.220 align:middle line:84%
portrayed, didn't
have any feelings,

00:08:03.220 --> 00:08:04.750 align:middle line:84%
didn't have any
inner experience,

00:08:04.750 --> 00:08:07.120 align:middle line:84%
was just kind of
there and observing,

00:08:07.120 --> 00:08:09.880 align:middle line:84%
