And to me, it's
this network that

00:15:55.130 --> 00:15:56.752 align:middle line:84%
runs the show of
what's happening

00:15:56.752 --> 00:15:57.710 align:middle line:90%
in our lives every day.

00:15:57.710 --> 00:16:02.360 align:middle line:84%
And I compare it to placing
classified ads in a newspaper

00:16:02.360 --> 00:16:04.220 align:middle line:84%
or sending emails
on the internet.

00:16:04.220 --> 00:16:06.710 align:middle line:84%
That all day long, we
are sending messages

00:16:06.710 --> 00:16:09.380 align:middle line:84%
into this network
asking for what we want

00:16:09.380 --> 00:16:11.940 align:middle line:84%
and offering to give
what we want to give.

00:16:11.940 --> 00:16:13.730 align:middle line:84%
And these messages
flash back and forth.

00:16:13.730 --> 00:16:16.490 align:middle line:84%
And at the unconscious level,
these directors and crew parts

00:16:16.490 --> 00:16:19.007 align:middle line:84%
of us behind the
scenes make deals.

00:16:19.007 --> 00:16:20.840 align:middle line:84%
We'll do this for you
if you do this for us.

00:16:20.840 --> 00:16:22.307 align:middle line:84%
And then something
happens up here

00:16:22.307 --> 00:16:24.140 align:middle line:84%
in what we call our
daily life, but it's all

00:16:24.140 --> 00:16:26.450 align:middle line:84%
generated by this
unconscious flow of activity

00:16:26.450 --> 00:16:27.990 align:middle line:84%
through this
unconscious network.

00:16:27.990 --> 00:16:28.790 align:middle line:90%
>> OK.

00:16:28.790 --> 00:16:29.870 align:middle line:90%
All right.

00:16:29.870 --> 00:16:32.690 align:middle line:84%
Well, now how does
reincarnation fall into this?

00:16:32.690 --> 00:16:36.210 align:middle line:84%
Do we just keep doing this until
we have our favorite movie?

00:16:36.210 --> 00:16:37.010 align:middle line:90%
[LAUGH]

00:16:37.010 --> 00:16:39.468 align:middle line:84%
>> Well, actually there's a
famous quote that's in the book

00:16:39.468 --> 00:16:42.455 align:middle line:84%
that was from Carl Jung, who
said that he had a feeling,

00:16:42.455 --> 00:16:44.510 align:middle line:84%
a very strong feeling
through his whole life--

00:16:44.510 --> 00:16:47.300 align:middle line:84%
this is Carl Jung-- that
there was some mystery that he

00:16:47.300 --> 00:16:51.540 align:middle line:84%
stumbled upon in a past life
that was just so rich that he

00:16:51.540 --> 00:16:54.930 align:middle line:84%
needed a bunch of lives to
be able to explore it fully.

00:16:54.930 --> 00:16:57.840 align:middle line:84%
So to me reincarnation
is, just like Tom Hanks,

00:16:57.840 --> 00:17:00.240 align:middle line:84%
in his lifetime,
may do 40 movies,

00:17:00.240 --> 00:17:02.730 align:middle line:84%
where he's doing 40
different things,

00:17:02.730 --> 00:17:04.700 align:middle line:84%
there's so many things
to do down here.

00:17:04.700 --> 00:17:06.450 align:middle line:84%
And we're fascinated
by all of the options

00:17:06.450 --> 00:17:08.200 align:middle line:84%
that we choose to come
back to play around

00:17:08.200 --> 00:17:10.500 align:middle line:84%
with some other reality,
either because we're not done

00:17:10.500 --> 00:17:12.167 align:middle line:84%
or because there's
something else to do.

00:17:12.167 --> 00:17:15.249 align:middle line:84%
Or you can think about a guy
like Mozart, who pops out

00:17:15.249 --> 00:17:17.803 align:middle line:84%
and as a kid is writing some
of the best music in the world.

00:17:17.803 --> 00:17:19.470 align:middle line:84%
>> I love that, yeah,
the four-year-old.

00:17:19.470 --> 00:17:21.595 align:middle line:84%
>> To me, that's a series
of lifetimes where he was

00:17:21.595 --> 00:17:24.359 align:middle line:84%
exploring musical composition,
and they culminated in that

00:17:24.359 --> 00:17:27.990 align:middle line:84%
life because he was fascinated
with that, for whatever reason.

00:17:27.990 --> 00:17:30.750 align:middle line:84%
>> One of the topics that you
cover here is that decision

00:17:30.750 --> 00:17:35.580 align:middle line:84%
making process, and we shouldn't
be worrying about the mistakes.

00:17:35.580 --> 00:17:39.580 align:middle line:84%
Because there wouldn't be,
then, any mistakes, would there?

00:17:39.580 --> 00:17:40.380 align:middle line:90%
>> No.

00:17:40.380 --> 00:17:41.330 align:middle line:90%
But let's say--

00:17:41.330 --> 00:17:42.630 align:middle line:90%
>> By your philosophy.

00:17:42.630 --> 00:17:45.780 align:middle line:84%
>> No, because by and large,
the director of your movie is

00:17:45.780 --> 00:17:47.580 align:middle line:90%
so capable of managing details.

00:17:47.580 --> 00:17:49.740 align:middle line:84%
But even if something
random happened,

00:17:49.740 --> 00:17:52.620 align:middle line:84%
or you were meant to go
left at a fork in the road

00:17:52.620 --> 00:17:54.690 align:middle line:84%
and you went right
instead, so the director

00:17:54.690 --> 00:17:56.940 align:middle line:84%
changes a couple of
scenes down the line

00:17:56.940 --> 00:17:58.722 align:middle line:84%
and gets you back
on track again.

00:17:58.722 --> 00:18:00.930 align:middle line:84%
But the thing that's so
important about that is there

00:18:00.930 --> 00:18:03.900 align:middle line:84%
was a time in my life when
I was at my most neurotic,

00:18:03.900 --> 00:18:06.450 align:middle line:84%
in any time there was a
big decision making point

00:18:06.450 --> 00:18:07.920 align:middle line:90%
in my life, I would freeze.

00:18:07.920 --> 00:18:10.308 align:middle line:84%
Because I thought,
I have this destiny.

00:18:10.308 --> 00:18:11.850 align:middle line:84%
And if I make the
wrong mistake here,

00:18:11.850 --> 00:18:13.308 align:middle line:84%
I'm going to trash
the whole thing,

00:18:13.308 --> 00:18:14.855 align:middle line:84%
and my life is
going to be ruined.

00:18:14.855 --> 00:18:16.480 align:middle line:84%
That's a little bit
of an exaggeration,

00:18:16.480 --> 00:18:18.450 align:middle line:90%
but I really would get nervous.

00:18:18.450 --> 00:18:21.270 align:middle line:84%
And being able to just
relax into the decisions

00:18:21.270 --> 00:18:24.818 align:middle line:84%
and trust that ultimately my
movie's going to get filmed.

00:18:24.818 --> 00:18:26.610 align:middle line:84%
I'm going to get to
experience what I want.

00:18:26.610 --> 00:18:28.110 align:middle line:84%
The director is
going to make sure

00:18:28.110 --> 00:18:30.810 align:middle line:84%
even if I make a mistake, quote
unquote, which I don't think

00:18:30.810 --> 00:18:35.820 align:middle line:84%
happens that much, it reduces
an enormous amount of stress

00:18:35.820 --> 00:18:37.890 align:middle line:84%
and lets you relax into
what's going on with you

00:18:37.890 --> 00:18:39.540 align:middle line:84%
and trusting this
director part of you

00:18:39.540 --> 00:18:42.280 align:middle line:84%
instead of being a worried
maniac all the time.

00:18:42.280 --> 00:18:44.220 align:middle line:90%
>> OK.

00:18:44.220 --> 00:18:47.550 align:middle line:84%
And what I kind
of wonder about is

00:18:47.550 --> 00:18:50.310 align:middle line:84%
some people really would
measure their success

00:18:50.310 --> 00:18:51.430 align:middle line:90%
by their happiness.

00:18:51.430 --> 00:18:52.230 align:middle line:90%
>> Right.

00:18:52.230 --> 00:18:54.600 align:middle line:90%
>> And you don't necessarily--

00:18:54.600 --> 00:18:59.280 align:middle line:84%
it's also just as good to be
totally bummed out because then

00:18:59.280 --> 00:19:02.440 align:middle line:84%
you're experiencing being
emotionally distressed.

00:19:02.440 --> 00:19:03.240 align:middle line:90%
Is that--

00:19:03.240 --> 00:19:05.790 align:middle line:84%
>> Well, there was a study that
was done earlier in the year,

00:19:05.790 --> 00:19:08.123 align:middle line:84%
where they interviewed a whole
bunch of people that went

00:19:08.123 --> 00:19:09.095 align:middle line:90%
to horror movies.

00:19:09.095 --> 00:19:11.470 align:middle line:84%
And they asked them why they
would go and watch all this.

00:19:11.470 --> 00:19:12.360 align:middle line:90%
>> Yes.

00:19:12.360 --> 00:19:16.870 align:middle line:84%
>> And a number of them said
there was something about that

00:19:16.870 --> 00:19:20.770 align:middle line:84%
feeling of being in massive fear
but safe at the same time that

00:19:20.770 --> 00:19:23.090 align:middle line:90%
I found really interesting.

00:19:23.090 --> 00:19:26.290 align:middle line:84%
So it comes down to
life is about exploring

00:19:26.290 --> 00:19:28.927 align:middle line:84%
your inner experiences
going on inside of you.

00:19:28.927 --> 00:19:30.760 align:middle line:84%
And we're interested
in exploring all of it.

00:19:30.760 --> 00:19:32.200 align:middle line:90%
And that involves feeling fear.

00:19:32.200 --> 00:19:33.550 align:middle line:90%
It involves being depressed.

00:19:33.550 --> 00:19:34.810 align:middle line:90%
And it involves being happy.

00:19:34.810 --> 00:19:37.690 align:middle line:84%
And it involves all of
the different emotions

00:19:37.690 --> 00:19:39.183 align:middle line:84%
that we experience
in a daily life.

00:19:39.183 --> 00:19:40.100 align:middle line:90%
None of them are good.

00:19:40.100 --> 00:19:41.020 align:middle line:90%
None of them are bad.

00:19:41.020 --> 00:19:42.820 align:middle line:84%
They're all part
of the experience.

00:19:42.820 --> 00:19:45.520 align:middle line:84%
>> Well, now one of your points
in managing and eliminating

00:19:45.520 --> 00:19:49.630 align:middle line:84%
your fears would be, then,
just to accept the fear.

00:19:49.630 --> 00:19:51.700 align:middle line:84%
Like I'm very easily
thrilled, so I

00:19:51.700 --> 00:19:54.130 align:middle line:84%
don't need to go on the
roller coasters and all

00:19:54.130 --> 00:19:57.010 align:middle line:90%
the really extreme rides.

00:19:57.010 --> 00:20:01.240 align:middle line:84%
And my husband enjoys those,
so he needs that kind of--

00:20:01.240 --> 00:20:04.540 align:middle line:84%
and there are people who want
to experience a level of fear

00:20:04.540 --> 00:20:07.210 align:middle line:84%
because that's what they
need for excitement?

00:20:07.210 --> 00:20:10.990 align:middle line:84%
>> Or because it moves them
in a particular direction.

00:20:10.990 --> 00:20:13.270 align:middle line:84%
To me, nothing
happens in your life

00:20:13.270 --> 00:20:15.070 align:middle line:84%
if there isn't
something about it that

00:20:15.070 --> 00:20:18.620 align:middle line:84%
is contributing to you exploring
to what you came here to do,

00:20:18.620 --> 00:20:20.710 align:middle line:84%
which is something that
fascinated you so much

00:20:20.710 --> 00:20:23.130 align:middle line:84%
that you wanted to explore
it at a very deep level.

00:20:23.130 --> 00:20:24.850 align:middle line:84%
Now, what the
specifics are, I can't

00:20:24.850 --> 00:20:27.880 align:middle line:84%
begin to guess, in my own life
or for other people's lives.

00:20:27.880 --> 00:20:30.310 align:middle line:84%
Sometimes when I do
consultations with people

00:20:30.310 --> 00:20:33.670 align:middle line:84%
and they talk about things,
you can begin to get clues.

00:20:33.670 --> 00:20:35.880 align:middle line:90%
But we're all different.

00:20:35.880 --> 00:20:36.770 align:middle line:90%
And there's no rules.

00:20:36.770 --> 00:20:39.490 align:middle line:84%
There's no formulas, except
to me, the generality.

00:20:39.490 --> 00:20:41.530 align:middle line:84%
You're exploring what
you came here to explore.

00:20:41.530 --> 00:20:42.370 align:middle line:90%
It's being managed.

00:20:42.370 --> 00:20:44.140 align:middle line:90%
You can't make a mistake.

00:20:44.140 --> 00:20:46.330 align:middle line:84%
And there are positive and
negative aspects to fear.

00:20:46.330 --> 00:20:47.410 align:middle line:90%
There are kinds of fear.

00:20:47.410 --> 00:20:50.380 align:middle line:84%
For example, if you were
in the jungle and all

00:20:50.380 --> 00:20:52.870 align:middle line:84%
of a sudden you saw a lion
jump out of the woods,

00:20:52.870 --> 00:20:54.430 align:middle line:84%
there would be some
positive aspects

00:20:54.430 --> 00:20:57.100 align:middle line:84%
to having fear come up
to make you cautious.

00:20:57.100 --> 00:21:01.060 align:middle line:84%
But when fear paralyzes you and
stops you from taking action

00:21:01.060 --> 00:21:03.042 align:middle line:84%
or just makes you feel
lousy all the time,

00:21:03.042 --> 00:21:04.750 align:middle line:84%
then perhaps it would
be valuable to look

00:21:04.750 --> 00:21:06.640 align:middle line:90%
at a way of changing it.

00:21:06.640 --> 00:21:09.340 align:middle line:84%
>> Now the response to
your book, you said,

00:21:09.340 --> 00:21:10.510 align:middle line:90%
has been very favorable.

00:21:10.510 --> 00:21:11.802 align:middle line:90%
You're very pleased with what--

00:21:11.802 --> 00:21:12.602 align:middle line:90%
>> Oh, yes.

00:21:12.602 --> 00:21:13.570 align:middle line:90%
>> --people are saying.

00:21:13.570 --> 00:21:15.820 align:middle line:84%
>> Yeah, because when I first
started on this journey,

00:21:15.820 --> 00:21:18.790 align:middle line:84%
I honest to god thought this is
weird Bob's solution to a tough

00:21:18.790 --> 00:21:21.828 align:middle line:84%
time, and it isn't going
to interest anybody else.

00:21:21.828 --> 00:21:23.620 align:middle line:84%
But I started sharing
it with other people,

00:21:23.620 --> 00:21:25.180 align:middle line:84%
and other people
would say, well, you

00:21:25.180 --> 00:21:27.310 align:middle line:84%
know that idea about the
network, the director,

00:21:27.310 --> 00:21:28.290 align:middle line:90%
I find that valuable.

00:21:28.290 --> 00:21:29.090 align:middle line:90%
It's helpful.

00:21:29.090 --> 00:21:31.740 align:middle line:84%
And so I started offering
it more organized ways,

00:21:31.740 --> 00:21:33.490 align:middle line:84%
and the feedback has
just been tremendous.

00:21:33.490 --> 00:21:35.328 align:middle line:84%
So I wrote the book,
and I'm planning

00:21:35.328 --> 00:21:37.120 align:middle line:84%
to do a bunch of other
things in the future

00:21:37.120 --> 00:21:39.370 align:middle line:84%
to help share these ideas with
people that are interested

00:21:39.370 --> 00:21:40.170 align:middle line:90%
in them.

00:21:40.170 --> 00:21:42.800 align:middle line:84%
>> Well we are so pleased
that you did write the book.

00:21:42.800 --> 00:21:44.590 align:middle line:84%
It's interesting
and fascinating.

00:21:44.590 --> 00:21:49.990 align:middle line:84%
Because it is a different way of
looking at our lives, and that

00:21:49.990 --> 00:21:51.530 align:middle line:90%
will help some people.

00:21:51.530 --> 00:21:54.440 align:middle line:84%
And it's interesting because
each author has their readers.

00:21:54.440 --> 00:21:55.240 align:middle line:90%
>> Yeah.

00:21:55.240 --> 00:21:57.530 align:middle line:84%
>> Yes, so thank you
for serving them well.

00:21:57.530 --> 00:21:58.330 align:middle line:90%
>> My pleasure.

